videos.description: Hamidou Diallo passes to Quade Green in transition who puts in a nice bucket for the Wildcats in the first half.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Diallo hits Green for one-handed lay-up

videos.description: Hamidou Diallo gets by defenders and puts it in for the and -1 against Harvard in the first half.
videos.headline: Wildcats' Diallo weaves in for and-1 layup

videos.description: Hamidou Diallo grabs the rebound and sprints to the rim for a vicious one-handed dunk that doesn't make it in the basket in the end of the first half against Harvard.
videos.headline: Diallo shows speed but doesn't get finish

videos.description: Kentucky's Shai Gilgeous-Alexander finds Nick Richards for a sweet alley-oop dunk in the second half.
videos.headline: Gilgeous-Alexander connects with Richards for alley-oop

videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander's layup in the second half extends Kentucky's lead 74-54 against Harvard.
videos.headline: Gilgeous-Alexander gets by defenders for easy lay-in

videos.description: Despite beating Harvard 79-70, Kentucky head coach John Calipari knows it will be a process for the young Wildcats to be a great defensive team.
videos.headline: Calipari: 'We are still learning how to win'

videos.description: Wildcats head coach John Calipari is happy with the win, as Kentucky pulls away in the second half vs. the Crimson.
videos.headline: No. 7 Kentucky downs Harvard 79-70
